Purpose
The purpose of this assignment is to demonstrate your ability to:
1. Execute Linux commands within Python scripts.
2. Write scripts to back up files and directories.
3. Write scripts for archiving files and directories.

By completing this assignment, you will gain practical experience automating system administration tasks like backups and archiving using Python.
Skills and knowledge gained
- Executing external Linux commands from Python scripts.
- Writing Python functions to perform backups and archiving.
- Handling files and directories programmatically, including error handling.
- Working with compressed archive formats (zip, tar, gztar, etc.).
- Retrieving file metadata such as size and last modification time.
